02/02/2011
ZAGREB, Croatia -- President Ivo Josipovic announced on Tuesday (February 1st) that Army Chief of Staff General Josip Lucic will be replaced by Major General Drago Lovric, Croatia's current military representative to NATO. 
Josipovic said the decision was part of reforms in the armed forces and alignment to Alliance standards. 
Prime Minister Jadranka Kosor says the government will formally propose Lovric on Thursday, with his appointment expected next week. 
(Nova TV, HRT, tportal.hr, Radio Free Europe, RTS - 01/02/11)
